[2]
Date: Wed 18 Sep 2002
From: "smacbean" <s.macbean@sasktel.net>
Source: Government of Manitoba, news release, bulletin 27, Wed 18 Sep 2002
[edited]
<http://www.gov.mb.ca/cgi-bin/press/release.pl>

Manitoba: West Nile Virus Update
--------------------------------
Mosquito pools:
Five more positive mosquito pools have been identified in Winkler (3) and in
Winnipeg (2), bringing the total to 15 positive pools so far this year.
These most recent pools of mosquitoes were collected between 26 and 27 Aug
2002.
Birds:
Five more birds have tested positive for West Nile virus: A crow in Portage
la Prairie, a raven and a crow in Winnipeg, a magpie in the RM of Ritchot,
and a magpie in the RM of Tache. The total number of confirmed positive
birds from the crow family is 78.
Sentinel chickens:
Three sentinel chickens from the northeast sector of Winnipeg have tested
presumptive positive for West Nile virus.
Equines:
Confirmation has been made on 9 of the 14 pending horse results reported
last week in Bulletin #26: RM of Wallace (2), RM of North Cypress (2), RM of
Rossburn (1), RM of Tache (1), RM of Springfield (1), RM of Blanshard (1),
RM of South Norfolk (1). The total number of confirmed positive horses in
Manitoba is 96.
--
smacbean
<s.macbean@sasktel.net>
